label.value: Normoblastic Erythroid Hyperplasia

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating an abnormally high quantity of immature red blood cells containing hemoglobin and a pyknotic nucleus.

label.value: Leukoerythroblastic Reaction

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating the presence of nucleated red blood cells and immature leukocytes in the peripheral blood. It is observed in disorders causing extramedullary hematopoiesis such as myelofibrosis and metastatic cancer to the bone marrow.

label.value: Myeloblasts Under 10 Percent of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating less than 10 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Benign Conjunctival Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the conjunctiva and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Blasts Under 20 Percent of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that less than 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral leukocyte sample are immature mononuclear cells.

label.value: Myeloblasts Under 5 Percent of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that less than 5 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral leukocyte sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Myeloblasts 5-19 Percent of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that 5-19 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral leukocyte sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Myeloblasts Under 20 Percent of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating less than 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral leukocyte sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Hemoglobin F Increased

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating an abnormal amount of fetal hemoglobin in a biological sample.

label.value: Ring Sideroblasts Under 15 Percent of Erythroid Precursors

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating less than 15 percent of the cells in a sample of erythroid precursor cells are ring sideroblasts.

label.value: Ring Sideroblasts 15 Percent or More of Erythroid Precursors

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating 15 percent or more of the cells in a sample of erythroid precursor cells are ring sideroblasts.

label.value: Bi-Cytopenia

value.value: A deficiency of two of the three blood cell lineages; erythrocytes, leukocytes and platelets.

label.value: Myeloblasts Under 1 Percent of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating less than 10 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral blood sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Myeloblasts 5-19 Percent of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that 5-19 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Benign Corneal Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the cornea and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Myeloblasts 5-9 Percent of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that between 5 and 9 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Myeloblasts 20 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Myeloblasts 20 Percent or More of Peripheral Blood White Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a peripheral leukocyte sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Bone Marrow Eosinophilia

value.value: A finding indicating abnormally high levels of eosinophils in a bone marrow sample.

label.value: Peripheral Blood Eosinophilia

value.value: A finding indicating abnormally high levels of eosinophils in a peripheral blood sample.

label.value: Bone Marrow Dysplasia Present

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating abnormal bone marrow cells.

label.value: Bone Marrow Dysplasia Present in 50 Percent or More of the Cells of Two Cell Lines

value.value: An indication that signs of dysplasia were detected in at least 50 percent of the cells from two hematopoietic cell lineages in a bone marrow sample

label.value: Bone Marrow Dysplasia Present in 10 Percent or More of the Cells of Two or More Myeloid Cell Lines

value.value: An indication that signs of dysplasia were detected in at least 10 percent of the cells from two myeloid cell lineages in a bone marrow sample

label.value: Promyelocytes, Myelocytes, and Mature Neutrophils 10 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 10 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are promyelocytes, myelocytes, and mature neutrophils.

label.value: Neoplastic Monocytes and Precursors 20 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are neoplastic mononcytes.

label.value: Benign Retinal Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the retina and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Monoblasts 20 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 20 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononcytes.

label.value: Monoblasts 80 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Monocytic Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 80 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononcytes.

label.value: Neoplastic Promonocytes in Bone Marrow Markedly Increased

value.value: An indication that the number of neoplastic promonocytes in a bone marrow sample have sharply increased when compared to a normal baseline or a previous sample measurement.

label.value: Erythroid Precursors 50 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 50 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature cells of the erythroid lineage.

label.value: Myeloblasts 20 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Non-Erythroid Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 20 percent of the non-erythroid nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature mononuclear cells of myeloid origin.

label.value: Erythroid Precursors 80 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 80 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature cells of the erythroid lineage.

label.value: Megakaryoblasts 50 Percent or More of Bone Marrow Nucleated Cells

value.value: A semi-quantitative microscopic finding indicating that at least 50 percent of the nucleated cells in a bone marrow sample are immature megakaryocytes.

label.value: Normal Bone Marrow Test Result

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating normal bone marrow cells.

label.value: Atypical Lymphocytes Present in Bone Marrow

value.value: A finding indicating that atypical lymphocytes were detected in a bone marrow sample.

label.value: Atypical Lymphocytes Present in Peripheral Blood

value.value: A variation of lymphocytes found in a peripheral blood smear that are larger, with abundant cytoplasm, and having nuclei with multiple nucleoli.

label.value: Benign Choroid Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the choroid and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Auer Rods Present
Benzene Exposure

value.value: Environmental, occupational or consumer-based exposure to benzene, benzene-containing compounds or benzene derivatives.

label.value: Ineffective Hematopoiesis

value.value: A dysfunction in the production of blood cells, resulting in decreased numbers of mature, functioning blood cells of all lines in circulation.

label.value: Bone Marrow Basophilia

value.value: A finding indicating abnormally high levels of basophils in a bone marrow sample.

label.value: Peripheral Blood Basophilia

value.value: A finding indicating abnormally high levels of basophils in a peripheral blood sample.

label.value: Secondary Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from a pre-existing lower grade lesion, or as a result of a primary lesion that has spread to secondary sites, or due to a complication of a cancer treatment.

label.value: Hematogenous Spread
Intravascular Spread
Lymphatic Spread
Acute Promyelocytic Leukemia with t(15;17)(q22;q12); PML/RARA
Benign Nasolacrimal Duct Neoplasm

value.value: A neoplasm that arises from the lacrimal duct and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Hereditary Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: Hereditary clear cell renal cell carcinoma associated with biallelic loss/inactivation of the von Hippel-Lindau tumor suppressor gene.

label.value: Non-Hereditary Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: The most common type of renal cell carcinoma, characterized by a loss of genetic material of the short arm of chromosome 3.  The most common symptom at the time of diagnosis is hematuria.  The tumor has a golden-yellow color because of the abundance of intracytoplasmic lipid.  This is a clinically aggressive type of renal cell carcinoma.  The tumor usually metastasizes to unusual sites and late metastasis is common.
